# School Management System Design Documentation

This document provides a technical overview of the School Management System, including its architecture, database schema, and key functional flows.

## 1. High-Level Architecture

The system follows a modern **MERN-like** architecture (using Node.js instead of React for the frontend in this specific iteration) with external service integrations for messaging and AI.

```mermaid
graph TD
    subgraph Client_Side [Frontend]
        UI[Browser / HTML & CSS]
        JS[Vanilla JavaScript / Fetch API]
    end

    subgraph Server_Side [Backend - Node.js & Express]
        API[Express API]
        Controller[Controllers]
        Service[Services]
        Model[Mongoose Models]
    end

    subgraph External_Services
        WhatsApp[WhatsApp-Web.js]
        Ollama[Ollama AI / Llama 3.1]
    end

    subgraph Database
        MongoDB[(MongoDB)]
    end

    UI <--> JS
    JS <--> API
    API <--> Controller
    Controller <--> Service
    Controller <--> Model
    Model <--> MongoDB
    Service <--> WhatsApp
    Service <--> Ollama
```

## 2. Entity Relationship Diagram (ERD)

The system uses MongoDB to store data. Relationships are managed through ObjectIDs and references.

```mermaid
erDiagram
    User ||--o{ Class : "manages"
    User ||--o{ Attendance : "records"
    Class ||--o{ Student : "contains"
    Class ||--o{ Subject : "has"
    Student ||--o{ Attendance : "has records"
    Student ||--o{ Grade : "receives"
    Subject ||--o{ Grade : "associated with"
    Guardian ||--o{ Student : "responsible for"

    User {
        ObjectId _id
        string username
        string passwordHash
        string role "admin/teacher"
    }

    Student {
        ObjectId _id
        string firstName
        string lastName
        ObjectId classId
        string parentPhone
        float feeBalance
    }

    Class {
        ObjectId _id
        string name
        ObjectId teacherId
    }

    Attendance {
        ObjectId _id
        ObjectId studentId
        ObjectId moduleId
        date date
        string status "present/absent"
    }

    Guardian {
        ObjectId _id
        string firstName
        string phone
        ObjectIdArray students
    }
```

## 3. Core Functional Flows

### A. Attendance Marking & WhatsApp Notification
When a teacher marks a student as absent, the system automatically triggers a WhatsApp notification to the parent.

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant Teacher as Teacher UI
    participant Server as Express Server
    participant DB as MongoDB
    participant WA as WhatsApp Service
    participant Parent as Parent Phone

    Teacher->>Server: POST /api/attendance (status: absent)
    Server->>DB: Save Attendance Record
    Server->>DB: Fetch Student & Parent Details
    Server->>WA: sendMessage(parentPhone, "Student Absent")
    WA->>Parent: WhatsApp Notification Sent
    Server-->>Teacher: Success Response
```

### B. AI Tutor Interaction
Students can interact with an offline AI (Ollama) for educational support.

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant Student as Student UI
    participant Server as Express Server
    participant AI_Service as AI Service (Ollama)
    participant Model as Llama 3.1

    Student->>Server: POST /api/ai/tutor (question)
    Server->>AI_Service: generateAIResponse(prompt)
    AI_Service->>Model: Request Generation
    Model-->>AI_Service: Response Text
    AI_Service-->>Server: Formatted Response
    Server-->>Student: Return Answer
```

## 4. Component Structure

The project follows a modular structure to ensure scalability and maintainability:

- **`routes/`**: Handles HTTP request mapping.
- **`controllers/`**: Contains the business logic for each route.
- **`models/`**: Defines the data structure using Mongoose schemas.
- **`services/`**: Abstracts external integrations (WhatsApp, AI).
- **`public/`**: Contains static assets and frontend logic.

